:: Snow White {"position":"575,375","size":"100,100"}
Regardless of how you ended up here, it seems as if there's now no way out. 

And you can't just go knock on the dwarves' house, no! What consequences would that end up having for the story? As a librarian, that's not something that you'll end up considering. 

But just when you thought you might have given up all hope, you see a light near the dwarves' house, and ignoring your misgivings, you inch towards it...

[[Turn the page ->Follow the Light]]

<a title="Kathleen Conklin from Falls Church, USA, CC BY 2.0 &lt;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0&gt;, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Charlevoix_-_Mushroom_House_(1332872112).jpg"><img width="960" alt="Charlevoix - Mushroom House (1332872112)" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Charlevoix_-_Mushroom_House_%281332872112%29.jpg/960px-Charlevoix_-_Mushroom_House_%281332872112%29.jpg"></a>


:: Stay in the bushes {"position":"700,1550","size":"100,100"}
A munchkin trips over you, pushing you forward into the crowd that's gathering around the house, clearly excited to see what commotion is happening.

With this crowd, you think that if you wait any longer, you might not end up being able to get home. 

This is something that definetly needs to be done, and there's absolutely no getting around it. 

As fast as you can, you run up to the witch and touch the shoes. You quickly find yourself enveloped, once again, within the blinding yellow light.

