:: The End {"position":"675,2125","size":"100,100"}
''The End''

<a title="E. C. Mountfort (illustration), Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Peace_Prophecies_Concerning_the_End_of_the_War_-_2113468d.webp"><img width="960" alt="Peace Prophecies Concerning the End of the War." src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Peace_Prophecies_Concerning_the_End_of_the_War_-_2113468d.webp/960px-Peace_Prophecies_Concerning_the_End_of_the_War_-_2113468d.webp.png"></a>


:: The Grand Ball {"position":"575,800","size":"100,100"}
It only makes sense that you're in the middle of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cinderella">//Cinderella//</a>. After all, that was the book right next to Snow White (Yes, you know you need to reorganize the fairy tale section). 

Just then, a girl in the most beautiful silver gown and gold shoes walks up the stairs, a serious look on her face. 

That must be Cinderella. It makes sense, as in most versions of the story besides the Disney movie, her dress isn't blue. 

Your theory that touching the most iconic item from each book was what held the key to you returning home seems to not be plausible, as you notice that Cinderella's gold shoes, inarguably the most iconic items from this story.

But then you realized that for Snow White, you had to wait in the forest for hours until the evil queen showed up. Cinderella's shoes will probably only start glowing when she leaves the ball. After all, that's the most iconic moment from her tale. 

You look down, at your sloppy clothes, not even close to the dress code of the ball, and curse yourself for not thinking ahead. There's definitely no chance that you're going to that ball, where you'd stand out like a sore thumb.

So for now, the bushes are your home...

[[Turn the page ->When The Clock Strikes Midnight]]

<a title="Pierre-Auguste Renoir, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Pierre-Auguste_Renoir_-_Luncheon_of_the_Boating_Party_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg"><img width="960" alt="Pierre-Auguste Renoir - Luncheon of the Boating Party - Google Art Project" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Pierre-Auguste_Renoir_-_Luncheon_of_the_Boating_Party_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg/960px-Pierre-Auguste_Renoir_-_Luncheon_of_the_Boating_Party_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg"></a>


:: The Pea {"position":"175,1650","size":"100,100"}
This castle isn't any harder than anything that you've climbed before, and it doesn't take long before you discover the room with a bunch of mattresses. 

You let yourself in through the open window and immediately see the pile of mattresses, where you see a light shine through. How are you supposed to get the pea from underneath?

Just then, the prince barges through the door.

"What are you doing here?" he asks. 

So much for inconspiculously climbing up. 

He looks over at the pile of mattresses and suddenly grows excited. "Did you feel the pea underneath?"


:: The Wicked Witch {"position":"575,1400","size":"100,100"}
It doesn't take long for the Wicked Witch to show up.

Once that happens, you could've blinked and missed the house falling on her. Once it does, the bright light continues to emit from them. 

You grimace when you realize what needs to be done. You have to touch the shoes, while the witch is still wearing them. 

You wonder if the Good Witch can send you back to your time, but you shake your head, quickly ridding yourself of the thought. 

You should just act now. If you miss this opportunity, who knows if you'll ever be able to return home.

Dorothy is also slowly opening the door now. What do you do?

[[Run up and quickly touch the shoes]]
[[Stay in the bushes]]
[[Interact with Dorothy]]

<a title="W. W. Denslow, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"><img width="500" alt="The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Book Cover" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg/500px-The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"></a>


:: The Wizard of Oz {"position":"575,1275","size":"100,100"}
But <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz">//The Wonderful Wizard of Oz//</a> isn't a fairy tale. How did you end up "hopping" into it?

Then again, you do work in a library. It is a //little// bit expected that things would disorganized sometimes.

Even if <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz">//The Wonderful Wizard of Oz//</a> is from an entirely different and century than most fairy tales... You shake your head, as it's not important to focus on that right now. 

You look around at Munchkin County, which simply looks busy and filled with Munchkins going about their day. No sign of the Wicked Witch, or a flying house, yet. 

So for now, you just wait...

[[Turn the page ->The Wicked Witch]]

<a title="W. W. Denslow, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"><img width="500" alt="The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Book Cover" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg/500px-The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"></a>


:: Touch the apple. {"position":"575,625","size":"100,100"}
Despite your misgivings, you reach out and touch it. 

<a title="Image provided by Landsbókasafn Íslands, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Snow_White_Poisoned_Apple.png"><img width="500" alt="Snow White Poisoned Apple" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Snow_White_Poisoned_Apple.png/500px-Snow_White_Poisoned_Apple.png"></a>

(link: "What happens?")[
You feel a jolt in your body as you feel yourself teleported from the forest. When you come to, you're in the bushes next to the most elaborate staircase that you've ever seen, as people wearing fancy clothes climb up the stairs. 

You sigh. You're in the middle of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cinderella">//Cinderella//</a>.

<a title="Thomas Wolf, www.foto-tw.de, CC BY-SA 3.0 DE &lt;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/de/deed.en&gt;, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Neues_Rathaus_Hannover_2013.jpg"><img width="960" alt="Neues Rathaus Hannover 2013" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/89/Neues_Rathaus_Hannover_2013.jpg/960px-Neues_Rathaus_Hannover_2013.jpg"></a>

[[Turn the page ->The Grand Ball]]
]


:: When The Clock Strikes Midnight {"position":"575,925","size":"100,100"}
You find yourself drifting further and further into sleep, but you jolt yourself awake when you see a blinding yellow light peek through the bushes. 

That's odd, you note. It seems like you spent a little less time here than you did in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snow-White">//Snow White//</a>.

When you wake up, you see Cinderella hurredly coming down the stairs. And as expected, she leaves behind her shoe. You guess that it only started glowing once it fell off, but that's just your theory that you unfortunately couldn't confirm. 

Now's your chance to touch it, without anyone else from the story noticing. 

You quickly dart out of the bushes... but then immediately become face-to-face with the prince, who has the most confused look on his face, clearly aware that you aren't the same girl he was dancing with 10

Do you:
[[quickly touch the shoe and avoid looking at the prince?]]
[[say an awkward joke?]]
[[try to run away?]]

<a title="Auckland Museum, CC BY 4.0 &lt;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0&gt;, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Shoes,_pair_(AM_1996.115.4-5).jpg"><img width="960" alt="Shoes, pair (AM 1996.115.4-5)" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Shoes%2C_pair_%28AM_1996.115.4-5%29.jpg/960px-Shoes%2C_pair_%28AM_1996.115.4-5%29.jpg"></a>


:: Yes. {"position":"625,1775","size":"100,100"}
"Yes, I did feel it," you lie. "Can I see it, to know that I'm not making it up?"

"It's real," the prince says.

"Can we lift up all of these mattresses?"

The prince sighs. He clearly doesn't want to do it, but he obliges, probably because he's glad to finally met a "real" princess, whatever that means. 

At the bottom of the mattresses and featherbeds, is the pea that's still glowing. 

"Thanks," you tell the prince, as you touch the pea, becoming engulfed in the yellow light.

[[Turn the page ->End]]

<a title="Metropolitan Museum of Art, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Design_for_a_Canopy_Bed_MET_49.50.174.jpg"><img width="500" alt="Design for a Canopy Bed, drawing, anonymous, French, 18th century (MET, 49.50.174)" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Design_for_a_Canopy_Bed_MET_49.50.174.jpg/500px-Design_for_a_Canopy_Bed_MET_49.50.174.jpg"></a>


:: hal.tracks {"position":"900,100","size":"100,100"}
fairytale: ./eglencelab-fairytale-cartoon-background-music-341216.mp3


:: one fell on you. {"position":"575,250","size":"100,100"}
You misplace a book on one of the shelves, and oops! One large book fell on your head, and you find yourself sounded by yellow light. When you came to, you ended up in this forest, which you quickly discerned was from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snow-White">//Snow White//</a> because of the dwarves' house.

[[Turn the page->Snow White]]

<a title="William Bowen, illustrated by Maud and Miska Petersham, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png"><img width="500" alt="The Enchanted Forest Bowen Frontpiece c.png" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png/330px-The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png?_=20120724060820"></a>


:: quickly touch the shoe and avoid looking at the prince? {"position":"450,1125","size":"100,100"}
Without looking at the prince, you quickly touch the shoe, and find yourself enveloped by the blinding yellow light. 

When you come to again, you find yourself in yet another bush. Looking past it, you spot the iconic yellow brick road that's unmistakable.

Yup. You're in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz">//The Wonderful Wizard of Oz//</a>.

[[Turn the page ->The Wizard of Oz]]

<a title="W. W. Denslow, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"><img width="500" alt="The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Book Cover" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg/500px-The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"></a>


:: say an awkward joke? {"position":"700,1125","size":"100,100"}
"I guess we're all looking for these tonight?" You crack a joke to the prince, who looks confused and like he'd honestly be anywhere else. 

Embarrased, you pick up the shoe, convinced that it will take you to where you next need to go. 

It does, and when you next come to, you find yourself in yet another bush. Looking past it, you spot the iconic yellow brick road that's unmistakable.

Yup. You're in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz">//The Wonderful Wizard of Oz//</a>.

[[Turn the page ->The Wizard of Oz]]

<a title="W. W. Denslow, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"><img width="500" alt="The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Book Cover" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg/500px-The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"></a>


:: startup {"position":"275,100","size":"100,100"}
(set: $name to " ")

(track: 'fairytale', 'loop', true)
(track: 'fairytale', 'playwhenpossible')

(goto: "Beginning")


:: try to run away? {"position":"575,1125","size":"100,100"}
Quickly, you try to run away, but you end up tripping on the shoe laying on the steps anyway and find yourself engulfed by the bright yellow light. 

When you come to again, you find yourself in yet another bush. Looking past it, you spot the iconic yellow brick road that's unmistakable.

Yup. You're in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz">//The Wonderful Wizard of Oz//</a>.

[[Turn the page ->The Wizard of Oz]]

<a title="W. W. Denslow, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"><img width="500" alt="The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Book Cover" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg/500px-The_Wonderful_Wizard_of_Oz_Book_Cover.jpg"></a>


:: you picked up an interesting one to read. {"position":"700,250","size":"100,100"}
You soon find yourself surrounded by the most blinding bright yellow light. After a moment, you find yourself in this forest, which you quickly discerned was from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snow-White">//Snow White//</a> because of the dwarves' house. 

[[Turn the page->Snow White]]

<a title="William Bowen, illustrated by Maud and Miska Petersham, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png"><img width="500" alt="The Enchanted Forest Bowen Frontpiece c.png" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png/330px-The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png?_=20120724060820"></a>


:: you see a light emitting from one of the books on the shelf and pick it up. {"position":"450,250","size":"100,100"}
You soon find yourself surrounded by that most blinding bright yellow light. After a moment, you find yourself in this forest, which you quickly discerned was from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snow-White">//Snow White//</a> because of the dwarves' house. 

[[Turn the page->Snow White]]

<a title="William Bowen, illustrated by Maud and Miska Petersham, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png"><img width="500" alt="The Enchanted Forest Bowen Frontpiece c.png" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png/330px-The_Enchanted_Forest_Bowen_Frontpiece_c.png?_=20120724060820"></a>


